# Dockerignore for the gateway container build.
#
# The gateway Docker build context is the repository root (see `Makefile`
# target `.gateway-image.stamp`). The build needs:
#   - `networking/`    — gateway Dockerfile, addons, Corefile, entrypoint
#   - `sandboxd/`      — Rust workspace; a build stage compiles
#                        `sandbox-deny-logger` from sources
#
# Everything else is noise. The Rust `target/` directory alone is ~17 GB
# on a hot workstation, so without this file the build context upload to
# the Docker daemon would be prohibitively large and slow.

# Rust build artifacts (per-workspace target dir, ~10-20 GB hot)
sandboxd/target/

# Python virtualenvs and caches
tests/e2e/.venv/
**/__pycache__/
*.pyc
*.egg-info/

# Node / site tooling
site/node_modules/
site/dist/

# Editor / IDE state
.idea/
.obsidian/
.stfolder/
.trash/
*.swp

# Git plumbing — we don't need history inside the build
.git/
.gitignore

# Task tracker state (plans / progress) — not needed in the image
.tasks/

# Docs & top-level design notes — not consumed by the build
docs/
site/
*.md
!networking/**/*.md
!sandboxd/**/*.md

# Misc build stamps
.gateway-image.stamp
